ic for discriminating between an elementary\nHiggs boson and a composite one. We show that the contribution to the\ncosmological constant due to a composite Higgs boson is more tractable and\nunder control than the contribution due to an elementary Higgs boson, and is\npotentially completely under control if there is an underlying conformal\nsymmetry not just in a critical scaling matter sector, but equally in the\ngravity sector to which the matter sector couples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2016 17:59:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 Jan 2017 20:00:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-05"}
