th an edge-on bar. By\ncoupling metallicities and radial velocities we show that the metal poor\npopulation has a velocity dispersion that varies rather mildly with latitude.\nOn the contrary, the metal rich population has a low velocity dispersion far\nfrom the plane (b=-8.5), but it has a steeper gradient with latitude, becoming\nhigher than the metal poor one in the innermost field (b=-1). [abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Oct 2016 11:41:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-08"}
